{
  "easy": {
    "title": "Format a Text Passage with Inline Elements",
    "description": "Take a plain text passage and add appropriate inline HTML elements to format it semantically. Use strong, em, mark, sub, sup, code, small, abbr, q, and cite.",
    "starterCode": "<p>HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is the standard language for creating web pages. The first version of HTML was released in 1993. Since then, it has evolved significantly. Learning HTML is the first step to becoming a web developer. The formula for water is H2O. In physics, energy equals mass times the speed of light squared: E = mc2.</p>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Formatted Passage</title>\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: Georgia, serif; max-width: 800px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 18px; }\n    mark { background: #fff3cd; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 2px; }\n    code { background: #e8e8e8; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em; }\n    abbr { text-decoration: underline dotted; cursor: help; }\n    q { font-style: italic; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p><abbr title=\"HyperText Markup Language\">HTML</abbr> stands for <strong>HyperText Markup Language</strong>. It is the <em>standard</em> language for creating web pages. The first version of <abbr title=\"HyperText Markup Language\">HTML</abbr> was released in <mark>1993</mark>. Since then, it has evolved significantly. <small>Learning HTML is the first step to becoming a web developer.</small></p>\n  <p>The formula for water is H<sub>2</sub>O. In physics, energy equals mass times the speed of light squared: <code>E = mc<sup>2</sup></code>.</p>\n  <p>As <cite>Tim Berners-Lee</cite> said, <q>The web is more a social creation than a technical one.</q></p>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
  "medium": {
    "title": "Build an Inline Navigation Bar",
    "description": "Create a horizontal navigation bar using only inline and inline-block elements. Include at least 5 links with hover effects, icons (emoji), and a current-page indicator. Ensure proper spacing and alignment.",
    "starterCode": "<nav>\n  <a href=\"#\">Home</a>\n  <a href=\"#\">About</a>\n  <a href=\"#\">Services</a>\n  <a href=\"#\">Blog</a>\n  <a href=\"#\">Contact</a>\n</nav>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Inline Nav</title>\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; max-width: 900px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; background: #f5f7fa; }\n    nav { background: #2c3e50; padding: 0; border-radius: 8px; }\n    nav a {\n      display: inline-block;\n      color: white;\n      text-decoration: none;\n      padding: 16px 24px;\n      font-size: 16px;\n      transition: all 0.2s;\n      position: relative;\n    }\n    nav a:hover { background: #34495e; }\n    nav a:not(:last-child)::after {\n      content: '';\n      position: absolute;\n      right: 0;\n      top: 25%;\n      height: 50%;\n      width: 1px;\n      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);\n    }\n    nav a.current { background: #e74c3c; }\n    @media (max-width: 600px) {\n      nav a { display: block; text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }\n      nav a:not(:last-child)::after { display: none; }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Inline Navigation</h1>\n  <nav>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"current\">🏠 Home</a>\n    <a href=\"#\">ℹ️ About</a>\n    <a href=\"#\">🛠 Services</a>\n    <a href=\"#\">📝 Blog</a>\n    <a href=\"#\">📞 Contact</a>\n  </nav>\n  <p style=\"margin-top:30px;\">The navigation uses <code>display: inline-block</code> on the links. On mobile (&lt;600px), they stack vertically.</p>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
  "hard": {
    "title": "Build an Inline Text Editor Toolbar",
    "description": "Create a text editor toolbar using inline and inline-block elements. Include buttons for bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, code, subscript, superscript, and highlight. Buttons should have hover effects and active states. Use a container with font-size: 0 to remove whitespace gaps.",
    "starterCode": "<div class=\"toolbar\">\n  <button class=\"tool-btn\">B</button>\n  <button class=\"tool-btn\">I</button>\n  <button class=\"tool-btn\">U</button>\n  <button class=\"tool-btn\">S</button>\n  <button class=\"tool-btn\">Code</button>\n</div>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Editor Toolbar</title>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n    body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; max-width: 800px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px; background: #f0f2f5; }\n    h1 { color: #2c3e50; }\n    .toolbar {\n      background: white;\n      border: 1px solid #ddd;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      padding: 8px;\n      font-size: 0;\n      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);\n      margin-bottom: 16px;\n    }\n    .tool-btn {\n      display: inline-block;\n      font-size: 14px;\n      padding: 8px 14px;\n      margin: 2px;\n      background: transparent;\n      border: 1px solid transparent;\n      border-radius: 4px;\n      cursor: pointer;\n      transition: all 0.15s;\n      font-family: inherit;\n      vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n    .tool-btn:hover { background: #e8f4fd; border-color: #2980b9; }\n    .tool-btn:active, .tool-btn.active { background: #2980b9; color: white; border-color: #2980b9; }\n    .separator {\n      display: inline-block;\n      width: 1px;\n      height: 24px;\n      background: #ddd;\n      margin: 4px 6px;\n      vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n    .editor {\n      background: white;\n      border: 1px solid #ddd;\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      padding: 20px;\n      min-height: 200px;\n      font-size: 16px;\n      line-height: 1.8;\n      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);\n    }\n    .format-demo { margin-top: 20px; }\n    .format-demo mark { background: #fff3cd; padding: 2px 4px; }\n    .format-demo code { background: #e8e8e8; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Text Editor Toolbar</h1>\n  <div class=\"toolbar\">\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Bold\"><strong>B</strong></button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Italic\"><em>I</em></button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Underline\"><u>U</u></button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Strikethrough\"><s>S</s></button>\n    <span class=\"separator\"></span>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Code\">{ }</button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Subscript\">x<sub>2</sub></button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Superscript\">x<sup>2</sup></button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Highlight\"><mark style=\"background:#fff3cd;padding:2px 4px;\">A</mark></button>\n    <span class=\"separator\"></span>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Link\">🔗</button>\n    <button class=\"tool-btn\" title=\"Image\">🖼</button>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"editor format-demo\">\n    <p>This is a <strong>text editor</strong> toolbar built with <em>inline-block</em> elements. The toolbar uses <code>font-size: 0</code> to eliminate <mark>whitespace gaps</mark> between buttons. Each button has hover and active states for visual feedback.</p>\n    <p>H<sub>2</sub>O and E=mc<sup>2</sup> show subscript and superscript support.</p>\n  </div>\n  <p style=\"color:#666;font-size:14px;margin-top:12px;\">Toolbar uses inline-block elements with font-size: 0 on parent to remove gaps.</p>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
